Package: skellambrms
Title: Skellam and Related Discrete Difference Distributions as brms
    Custom Families
Version: 0.3.1
Authors@R: person("Adam N. H.", "Smith", , "anhsmith@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides custom brms families for modelling the difference
    between two paired count sources: the symmetric and asymmetric Skellam
    distributions (the distribution of the difference of two Poisson random
    variables), and discrete Laplace and discrete normal distributions
    discretised via CDF differencing. Each distribution is available with
    location fixed at zero (testing whether two sources agree on average)
    and with a free location parameter (quantifying systematic
    disagreement), all sampled on a common SD-scale spread parameter.
    Includes truncation support via brms's resp_trunc(). Intended for
    modelling set-level differences between paired count sources.
